<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lupinus</i> <i>arboreus</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Ammophila</i> <i>arenaria</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>ericoides</i> and <i>Lupinus</i> <i>chamissonis</i>. Emergent trees or tall shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Alnus</i> <i>rubra</i> or <i>Morella</i> <i>californica</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is variable. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Lupinus arboreus</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Lupinus arboreus</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy, or > 30% relative cover with <i>Baccharis pilularis</i> and/or <i>Rubus ursinus</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Stabilized dunes of coastal bars, backdunes, river mouths, spits along coastline; coastal bluffs, terraces.  </div>
</div>

        
